SPRIGATITO.description:
The sweet scent its body gives off
mesmerizes those around it. The
scent grows stronger when this
Pokémon is in the sun.

FLORAGATO.description:
Floragato deftly wields the vine
hidden beneath its long fur, slamming
the hard flower bud against its
opponents.

MEOWSCARADA.description:
This Pokémon uses the reflective
fur lining its cape to camouflage the
stem of its flower, creating the
illusion that the flower is floating.

FUECOCO.description:
Its flame sac is small, so energy is
always leaking out. This energy is
released from the dent atop
Fuecoco's head and flickers to and fro.

CROCALOR.description:
The combination of Crocalor's fire
energy and overflowing vitality has
caused an egg-shaped fireball to
appear on the Pokémon's head.

SKELEDIRGE.description:
Skeledirge's gentle singing
soothes the souls of all that hear it. It
burns its enemies to a crisp with
flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.

QUAXLY.description:
Its strong legs let it easily swim
around in even fast-flowing rivers.
It likes to keep things tidy and is
prone to overthinking things.

QUAXWELL.description:
The hardworking Quaxwell observes
people and Pokémon from various
regions and incorporates their
movements into its own dance routines.

QUAQUAVAL.description:
A single kick from a Quaquaval can
send a truck rolling. This Pokémon
uses its powerful legs to perform
striking dances from far-off lands.

LECHONK.description:
It searches for food all day. It
possesses a keen sense of smell but
doesn't use it for anything other
than foraging.

OINKOLOGNE_F.description:
This is a meticulous Pokémon that
likes to keep things tidy. It
shrouds itself in a floral aroma that
soothes the Pokémon around it.

OINKOLOGNE_M.description: Oinkologne is proud of its fine,\nglossy skin. It emits a concentrated\nscent from the tip of its tail.

TAROUNTULA.description:
The thread it secretes from its
rear is as strong as wire. The secret
behind the thread's strength is the
topic of ongoing research.

SPIDOPS.description:
It clings to branches and ceilings
using its threads and moves without
a sound. It takes out its prey
before the prey even notices it.

NYMBLE.description:
It has its third set of legs folded
up. When it's in a tough spot, this
Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the
strength of its legs.

LOKIX.description:
When it decides to fight all out, it
stands on its previously folded
legs to enter Showdown Mode. It
neutralizes its enemies in short order.

PAWMI.description:
The pads of its paws are electricity-
discharging organs. Pawmi fires
electricity from its forepaws while
standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

PAWMO.description:
When its group is attacked, Pawmo
is the first to leap into battle,
defeating enemies with a fighting
technique that utilizes electric shocks.

PAWMOT.description:
This Pokémon normally is slow to
react, but once it enters battle, it
will strike down its enemies with
lightning-fast movements.

TANDEMAUS.description:
Exhibiting great teamwork, they
use their incisors to cut pieces out
of any material that might be useful
for a nest, then make off with them.

MAUSHOLD_FOUR.description:
The larger pair protects the little
ones during battles. When facing
strong opponents, the whole group
will join the fight.

MAUSHOLD_THREE.description:
The little one just appeared one
day. They all live together like a
family, but the relationship between
the three is still unclear.

FIDOUGH.description:
This Pokémon is smooth and moist
to the touch. Yeast in Fidough's
breath induces fermentation in the
Pokémon's vicinity.

DACHSBUN.description:
The pleasant aroma that emanates
from this Pokémon's body helps
wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been
treasured by farming villages.

SMOLIV.description:
This Pokémon converts nutrients
into oil, which it stores in the fruit
on its head. It can easily go a whole
week without eating or drinking.

DOLLIV.description:
Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-
scented oil with others. This species
has coexisted with humans since
times long gone.

ARBOLIVA.description:
This Pokémon drives back enemies
by launching its rich, aromatic oil at
them with enough force to smash a
boulder.

SQUAWKABILLY_BLUE.description:
The largest of their flocks can
contain more than 50 individuals. They
fly around towns and forests,
searching for food and making a racket.

SQUAWKABILLY_GREEN.description:
Green-feathered flocks hold the
most sway. When they're out
searching for food in the mornings and
evenings, it gets very noisy.

SQUAWKABILLY_YELLOW.description:
These Squawkabilly are hotheaded,
and their fighting style is vicious.
They'll leap within reach of their
foes to engage in close combat.

SQUAWKABILLY_WHITE.description:
Though these Squawkabilly are the
fewest in number, they have no
trouble living in towns since they blend
in with the white buildings.

NACLI.description:
The ground scrapes its body as it
travels, causing it to leave salt
behind. Salt is constantly being created
and replenished inside Nacli's body.

NACLSTACK.description:
It compresses rock salt inside its
body and shoots out hardened salt
pellets with enough force to
perforate an iron sheet.

GARGANACL.description:
Garganacl will rub its fingertips
together and sprinkle injured
Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will
promptly heal afterward.

CHARCADET.description:
Burnt charcoal came to life and
became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery
fighting spirit, Charcadet will
battle even tough opponents.

ARMAROUGE.description:
Armarouge evolved through the use
of a set of armor that belonged to
a distinguished warrior. This
Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

CERULEDGE.description:
The fiery blades on its arms burn
fiercely with the lingering
resentment of a sword wielder who fell
before accomplishing their goal.

TADBULB.description:
Tadbulb shakes its tail to
generate electricity. If it senses danger,
it will make its head blink on and off
to alert its allies.

BELLIBOLT.description:
When this Pokémon expands and
contracts its wobbly body, the belly-
button dynamo in its stomach
produces a huge amount of electricity.

WATTREL.description:
When its wings catch the wind, the
bones within produce electricity.
This Pokémon dives into the ocean,
catching prey by electrocuting them.

KILOWATTREL.description:
It uses its throat sac to store
electricity generated by its wings.
There's hardly any oil in its feathers,
so it is a poor swimmer.

MASCHIFF.description:
Its well-developed jaw and fangs
are strong enough to crunch through
boulders, and its thick fat makes
for an excellent defense.

MABOSSTIFF.description:
Mabosstiff loves playing with
children. Though usually gentle, it
takes on an intimidating look when
protecting its family.

SHROODLE.description:
To keep enemies away from its
territory, it paints markings around its
nest using a poisonous liquid that
has an acrid odor.

GRAFAIAI.description:
Each Grafaiai paints its own
individual pattern, and it will paint that
same pattern over and over again
throughout its life.

BRAMBLIN.description:
A soul unable to move on to the
afterlife was blown around by the wind
until it got tangled up with dried
grass and became a Pokémon.

BRAMBLEGHAST.description:
It will open the branches of its
head to envelop its prey. Once it
absorbs all the life energy it needs, it
expels the prey and discards it.

TOEDSCOOL.description:
Though it looks like Tentacool,
Toedscool is a completely different
species. Its legs may be thin, but it
can run at a speed of 30 mph.

TOEDSCRUEL.description:
These Pokémon gather into groups
and form colonies deep within
forests. They absolutely hate it when
strangers approach.

KLAWF.description:
Klawf hangs upside-down from
cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can't
remain in this position for long
because its blood rushes to its head.

CAPSAKID.description:
The more sunlight this Pokémon
bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are
produced by its body, and thus the
spicier its moves become.

SCOVILLAIN.description:
The green head has turned vicious
due to the spicy chemicals
stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a
rampage, there is no stopping it.

RELLOR.description:
This Pokémon creates a mud ball by
mixing sand and dirt with psychic
energy. It treasures its mud ball more
than its own life.

RABSCA.description:
The body that supports the ball
barely moves. Therefore, it is thought
that the true body of this Pokémon
is actually inside the ball.

FLITTLE.description:
Flittle's toes levitate about half
an inch above the ground because of
the psychic power emitted from the
frills on the Pokémon's belly.

ESPATHRA.description:
It immobilizes opponents by
bathing them in psychic power from its
large eyes. Despite its appearance, it
has a vicious temperament.

TINKATINK.description:
This Pokémon pounds iron scraps
together to make a hammer. It will
remake the hammer again and again until
it's satisfied with the result.

TINKATUFF.description:
These Pokémon make their homes in
piles of scrap metal. They test the
strength of each other's hammers by
smashing them together.

TINKATON.description:
The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it
gets swung around easily by
Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases
and carries its plunder back home.

WIGLETT.description: This Pokémon can pick up the scent\nof a Veluza just over 65 feet away\nand will hide itself in the sand.

WUGTRIO.description: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio\nwas once considered to be a\nregional form of Dugtrio.

BOMBIRDIER.description:
Bombirdier uses the apron on its
chest to bundle up food, which it
carries back to its nest. It enjoys
dropping things that make loud noises.

FINIZEN.description: Its water ring is made from\nseawater mixed with a sticky fluid that\nFinizen secretes from its blowhole.

PALAFIN_HERO.description:
This Pokémon's ancient genes have
awakened. It is now so extraordinarily
strong that it can easily lift a
cruise ship with one fin.

PALAFIN_ZERO.description:
This Pokémon changes its appearance
if it hears its allies calling for
help. Palafin will never show
anybody its moment of transformation.

VAROOM.description:
The steel section is Varoom's
actual body. This Pokémon clings to
rocks and converts the minerals within
into energy to fuel its activities.

REVAVROOM.description:
It creates a gas out of poison and
minerals from rocks. It then
detonates the gas in its cylinders- now
numbering eight-to generate energy.

CYCLIZAR.description:
It can sprint at over 70 mph while
carrying a human. The rider's body
heat warms Cyclizar's back and lifts
the Pokémon's spirit.

ORTHWORM.description:
When attacked, this Pokémon will
wield the tendrils on its body like
fists and pelt the opponent with a
storm of punches.

GLIMMET.description:
Glimmet's toxic mineral crystals
look just like flower petals. This
Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like
pollen to protect itself.

GLIMMORA.description:
Glimmora's petals are made of
crystallized poison energy. It has
recently become evident that these
petals resemble Tera Jewels.

GREAVARD.description:
This friendly Pokémon doesn't like
being alone. Pay it even the
slightest bit of attention, and it will
follow you forever.

HOUNDSTONE.description:
Houndstone spends most of its
time sleeping in graveyards. Among all
the dog Pokémon, this one is most
loyal to its master.

FLAMIGO.description:
Thanks to a behavior of theirs
known as “synchronizing,” an entire
flock of these Pokémon can attack
simultaneously in perfect harmony.

CETODDLE.description:
This species left the ocean and
began living on land a very long time
ago. It seems to be closely related
to Wailmer.

CETITAN.description:
Ice energy builds up in the horn on
its upper jaw, causing the horn to
reach cryogenic temperatures that
freeze its surroundings.

VELUZA.description:
Veluza has excellent regenerative
capabilities. It sheds spare flesh
from its body to boost its agility,
then charges at its prey.

DONDOZO.description:
It treats Tatsugiri like its boss
and follows it loyally. Though
powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very
smart.

TATSUGIRI_CURLY.description:
This is a small dragon Pokémon. It
lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to
protect itself from enemies on the
outside.

TATSUGIRI_DROOPY.description: This Pokémon tricks its opponents\nby playing dead. It is small and\nweak, but it uses its smarts to survive.

TATSUGIRI_STRETCHY.description: It's one of the most intelligent\ndragon Pokémon. It camouflages itself\nby inflating its throat sac.

GREAT_TUSK.description:
Sightings of this Pokémon have
occurred in recent years. The name
Great Tusk was taken from a creature
listed in a certain book.

SCREAM_TAIL.description:
There has been only one reported
sighting of this Pokémon. It
resembles a mysterious creature depicted
in an old expedition journal.

BRUTE_BONNET.description:
It bears a slight resemblance to a
Pokémon described in a dubious
magazine as a cross between a dinosaur
and a mushroom.

FLUTTER_MANE.description:
It has similar features to a
ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a
paranormal magazine, but the two
have little else in common.

SLITHER_WING.description: This mysterious Pokémon has some\nsimilarities to a creature that an\nold book introduced as Slither Wing.

SANDY_SHOCKS.description:
It slightly resembles a Magneton
that lived for 10,000 years and was
featured in an article in a
paranormal magazine.

IRON_TREADS.description:
Sightings of this Pokémon have
occurred in recent years. It resembles
a mysterious object described in an
old expedition journal.

IRON_BUNDLE.description:
Its shape is similar to a robot
featured in a paranormal magazine
article. The robot was said to have been
created by an ancient civilization.

IRON_HANDS.description:
It is very similar to a cyborg
covered exclusively by a paranormal
magazine. The cyborg was said to be the
modified form of a certain athlete.

IRON_JUGULIS.description:
It resembles a certain Pokémon
introduced in a paranormal magazine,
described as the offspring of a
Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.

IRON_MOTH.description:
No records exist of this species
being caught. Data is lacking, but
the Pokémon's traits match up with an
object described in an old book.

IRON_THORNS.description:
It has some similarities to a
Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine
as a Tyranitar from one billion
years into the future.

FRIGIBAX.description:
This Pokémon lives in forests and
craggy areas. Using the power of its
dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its
nest like a refrigerator.

ARCTIBAX.description:
Arctibax freezes the air around it,
protecting its face with an ice
mask and turning its dorsal fin into a
blade of ice.

BAXCALIBUR.description:
It launches itself into battle by
flipping upside down and spewing
frigid air from its mouth. It finishes
opponents off with its dorsal blade.

GIMMIGHOUL_CHEST.description:
It lives inside an old treasure
chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop
corners since no one realizes it's
actually a Pokémon.

GIMMIGHOUL_ROAMING.description:
It wanders around, carrying an old
coin on its back. It survives by
draining the life-force from humans who
try to pick up its coin.

GHOLDENGO.description:
It has a sturdy body made up of
stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms
its enemies by firing coin after coin
at them in quick succession.

WO_CHIEN.description:
The grudge of a person punished
for writing the king's evil deeds upon
wooden tablets has clad itself in
dead leaves to become a Pokémon.

CHIEN_PAO.description:
This Pokémon can control 100 tons
of fallen snow. It plays around
innocently by leaping in and out of
avalanches it has caused.

TING_LU.description:
It slowly brings its exceedingly
heavy head down upon the ground,
splitting the earth open with huge
fissures that run over 160 feet deep.

CHI_YU.description:
It controls flames burning at over
5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It
casually swims through the sea of lava it
creates by melting rock and sand.

ROARING_MOON.description:
According to an article in a
dubious magazine, this Pokémon has some
connection to Mega Evolution that
occurs in Hoenn.

IRON_VALIANT.description: It has some similarities to a mad\nscientist's invention covered in a\nparanormal magazine.

KORAIDON.description:
This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar,
but it is far burlier and more
ferocious. Nothing is known about its
ecology or other features.

MIRAIDON.description:
This seems to be the Iron Serpent
mentioned in an Violet Book. The
Iron Serpent is said to have turned the
land to ash with its lightning.

WALKING_WAKE.description: This ferocious creature is shrouded in\nmystery. It's named after an aquatic\nmonster mentioned in an old journal.

IRON_LEAVES.description: According to the few eyewitness accounts\nthat exist, it used its shining blades\nto julienne large trees and boulders.

POLTCHAGEIST_ARTISAN.description:
It has taken up residence in a very
expensive tea caddy. It takes an
expert to distinguish the expensive
tea caddies from the cheap ones.

POLTCHAGEIST_COUNTERFEIT.description:
Supposedly, the regrets of a tea
ceremony master who died before
perfecting his craft lingered in some
matcha and became a Pokémon.

SINISTCHA_MASTERPIECE.description:
The more stirring it does with the
tea whisk on its head, the more
energy it builds up. It does this to
prepare for battle.

SINISTCHA_UNREMARKABLE.description:
It pretends to be tea, trying to fool
people into drinking it so it can
drain their life-force. Its ruse is
generally unsuccessful.

OKIDOGI.description:
After all its muscles were stimulated
by the toxic chain around its neck,
Okidogi transformed and gained
a powerful physique.

MUNKIDORI.description:
The chain is made from toxins that
enhance capabilities. It stimulated
Munkidori's brain and caused the
Pokémon's psychic powers to bloom.

FEZANDIPITI.description:
Fezandipiti owes its beautiful looks and
lovely voice to the toxic stimulants
emanating from the chain wrapped around
its body.

GOUGING_FIRE.description:
There are scant few reports of
this creature being sighted.
One short video shows it rampaging,
and spouting pillars of flame.

RAGING_BOLT.description:
It bears resemblance to a Pokémon
that became a hot topic for a short
while after a paranomal magazine
touted it as Raikou's ancestor.

IRON_BOULDER.description: It was named after a mysterious\nobject recorded in an old book.\nIts body seems to be metallic.

IRON_CROWN.description:
It resembles a mysterious object
introduced in a paranormal magazine
as a cutting-edge weapon
shaped like Cobalion.

TERAPAGOS_NORMAL.description:
Terapagos protects itself using its
power to transform energy into hard
crystals. This Pokémon is the source
of the Terastal phenomenon.

TERAPAGOS_TERASTAL.description:
The shell is made of crystallized
Terastal energy. When struck by a move,
this shell absorbs the move's energy
and transfers it to Terapagos.

TERAPAGOS_STELLAR.description:
An old expedition journal describes the
sight of this Pokémon buried in the,
depths of the earth as resembling a
planet floating in space.

PECHARUNT.description:
It feeds others toxic mochi that
draw out desires and capabilities.
Those who eat the mochi fall under
Pecharunt's control, chained to its will.
